name Esterházy-Slices
serves 1 tray
tags cake, nuts, fruit
related punschtorte

# For the hazelnut joconde

- 360 g ground hazelnuts
-> roasted hazelnuts
Roast the hazelnuts in a large pan while stirring continuously. Splitting it into
several portions may be helpful.

- 15 "egg whites"
- 360 g sugar
- salt
- 150 g flour
= roasted hazelnuts
-> sponge layers
Whip 5 egg whites, 120g sugar and a dash of salt until stiff. Mix in 50g of flour and 120g
of the roasted hazelnuts. Spread on a baking tray and bake at 190°C for 12 minutes. Repeat
for a total of {3} plates.


# For the filling

- 300 g dried apricots
- 200 ml orange juice
- 200 g marzipan
-> marzipan filling
Bring the orange juice to a boil. Chop the apricots and add to the orange juice. Put aside
for 20 to 30 minutes, then knead with the marzipan to produce a homogeneous mass.

- 400 g nougat
- 125 ml cream
-> nougat filling
Melt nougat and cream

= sponge layers
= marzipan filling
= nougat filling
- 100 g chopped hazelnuts
<p>Spread the marzipan filling on one sponge. Layer the next sponge on top and press down
firmly. Spread ¾ of the nougat filling on top. Layer the third sponge as well. Spread the remaining 
nougat filling on top, followed by the chopped hazelnuts. Refridgerate.</p>
<p>Optionally one may use crushed hazelnut praline instead of plain hazelnuts.</p>